# Olivetti M20 FUZIX Port — TODO

## Critical: exec binary loading
  readi during exec claims done=40 (success) but data reads back as
  zeros from the destination address. Direct writes and manual code
  injection work fine at the same address. The issue is in the
  blktok/blktou → memcpy/_uput path during readi.

  Current workaround: manual code injection in syscall_exec32.c.

  Investigation leads:
  - Check if memcpy destination pointer is correct at call time
  - Add debug prints inside readi loop (uputblk call)
  - Check if umove advances u_base correctly with 32-bit pointers
  - Verify blktok macro expansion produces correct argument order
  - Test with CONFIG_LARGE_IO_DIRECT disabled
  - May be another WORD_REGISTER_OPERATIONS-class codegen bug

## Critical: user-space toolchain
  - Build crt0 for Z8001 user programs (VDSO syscall stub)
  - Syscall wrappers (write, read, open, _exit, fork, exec, wait)
  - Cross-compile newlib or FUZIX libc for Z8001
  - Build /init, /bin/sh, basic utils

## Critical: process management
  - dofork (tricks.S) — currently a stub returning 0
  - switchin/switchout — skeleton exists, needs testing
  - Signal delivery — return_via_signal is a TODO stub
  - d_open return value check — removed, needs restoring

## Important: drivers
  - Keyboard input — serial RxRDY polling works in tty_interrupt,
    needs a user program that reads stdin to test
  - Floppy driver — same BIOS disk_io interface as HD
  - Video console — MC6845 framebuffer at segment 3
  - Keyboard USART — i8251A at 0xA1/0xA3 with M20 keyboard protocol

## Important: memory management
  - Multi-segment user processes (use seg A/C/D/E for larger programs)
  - Per-segment allocation instead of single flat pool
  - SYS_HDPRES workaround — find why BIOS workspace gets cleared

## Compiler bugs (workarounds in place)
  - WORD_REGISTER_OPERATIONS: FIXED in gcc — byte ops don't extend
  - Jump table codegen: FIXED — CASE_VECTOR_MODE HImode
  - addr(Rn) register: FIXED — use low word of pair
  - Register global asm("r10"): WORKAROUND — -ffixed-r10
  - Need to run GCC torture tests to find more bugs

## Nice to have
  - RTC / timekeeping
  - Printer driver (i8255A parallel port)
  - Proper build system integration (make from Kernel/ root)
